# Defect Report — AMS R1 Respond to Findings: Subdivided Parcel Option Incorrectly Present

-----

## Defect Summary

**Title:** AMS R1 — Subdivided Parcel Option Incorrectly Displayed Under Accept/Reject Findings When Selecting Accept

**Jira ID:** BISSAGL-X
**Severity:** Medium
**Priority:** High
**Type:** Defect
**Component:** AMS — Respond to Findings — Accept/Reject
**Environment:** CENTEST
**Round:** Round 1 — 2026
**Application:** Basic Income Support for Sustainability (BISS)
**Reported by:** Aniket Pathare | aniket.pathare@government.ie
**Date:** 28-Apr-2026

-----

## Description

When a user logged in under an AMS Round 1 profile navigates to the AMS tab in My Clients,
searches for a herd or parcel, clicks View, then proceeds to respond to AMS findings via the
Respond to Findings button on the Farmer Dashboard, searches for the parcel, and under the
Accept / Reject Findings section clicks the Select Option dropdown and selects **Accept** —
the **Subdivided Parcel** option is incorrectly displayed. This option should not be present
at any point in the AMS Round 1 respond to findings flow. Its presence is unintended and
constitutes a display defect for AMS R1 profile users.

-----

## Steps to Reproduce

1. Log in to BISS on CENTEST using an AMS Round 1 profile agent account
   *(Use SQL Query below to find a herd with Round 1 AMS findings)*
1. Navigate to **My Clients** via the left menu
1. Click on the **AMS** tab on the My Clients page
1. In the AMS tab search field, enter the **parcel number or herd number**
1. Click **Search** — one row should be returned in the results
1. Click **View** on that row
1. User lands on the **Farmer Dashboard**
1. Click the **Respond to Findings** button on the AMS Findings panel
1. On the AMS response screen, search for the **parcel number**
1. Locate the parcel row under the **Accept / Reject Findings** section
1. Click the **Select Option** dropdown on the parcel row
1. Select **Accept** from the dropdown options
1. Observe the options displayed after selecting Accept

-----

## Actual Result

After selecting **Accept** under the Accept / Reject Findings section, the **Subdivided Parcel**
option is incorrectly displayed. This option should not be available to AMS R1 profile users
at any point in the respond to findings flow.

-----

## Expected Result

The **Subdivided Parcel** option should **NOT** be present in the AMS Round 1 respond to
findings flow after selecting Accept under Accept / Reject Findings. Only options relevant
to responding to an AMS Round 1 finding should be displayed at this stage.

-----

## Impact

- AMS R1 profile users are exposed to the Subdivided Parcel option during the respond to
  findings flow — a feature that is out of scope for this profile and this round
- A user could incorrectly trigger a sub-division action on a parcel during an AMS response
- Sub-division actioned incorrectly could affect parcel eligibility calculations and
  introduce data integrity issues in the BISS application for the affected herd
- Violates expected access control for AMS R1 profile users in the respond to findings flow

-----

## Test Data

```sql
-- Find herd with AMS Round 1 findings (CENTEST_BISS_DATA)
-- Query 70 from reference document
SELECT *
FROM VWBS_AMS_NOTIFIED_HERD
WHERE scheme_year = 2026
AND   expired     = 0
AND   ROWNUM <= 5
ORDER BY herd_no;
```

```sql
-- Get agent login for herd (CENTEST_BISS_INET)
SELECT hbcus.bcus_bus_id   AS HERDNO,
       MIN(ui.uri_username) AS USERNAME
  FROM tdco_customer_asscs ca,
       tdco_business_customers abcus,
       tdco_business_customers hbcus,
       tdcr_user_info ui
 WHERE SYSDATE BETWEEN ca.ca_start_date AND ca.ca_end_date
   AND ca.ca_cac_code     = 194
   AND ca.ca_bcus_id_from = abcus.bcus_id
   AND ca.ca_bcus_id_to   = hbcus.bcus_id
   AND ui.uri_ccs_bus_id  = abcus.bcus_bus_id
   AND hbcus.bcus_bus_id  = '<HERD_NUMBER_FROM_ABOVE>'
 GROUP BY hbcus.bcus_bus_id
HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT ui.uri_username) = 1;
```

-----

## Additional Notes

- Reproducible consistently for any herd with Round 1 AMS findings via the above flow
- The Subdivided Parcel option may be valid in other BISS flows (e.g. standard Land Details
